UTON.about:
BEHIND THE SCENES
Recorded & mixed between September-November 2019. Mastered in December 2019. Instruments used on this album: digital synths, effects, field recordings, flute, bells, vocals, bowl, found sounds.
Released on cassette by Black Horizons, 8th March 2021.
Edition of 77 copies.  www.black-horizons.com/news.html
"Uton, Jani Hirvonen, is back on Black Horizons with his new full length. An understated gem of blistering, buzzing, layered psychedelic noise. Buzzing insect noise, field recordings, looping rhythmic pulses all come together to create an immersive whole. Moving through 11 fairly short tracks that feel like meditative vignettes of the psyche, sometimes bright and ecstatic but often taking a turn for the ominous and sinister. Hence the appropriate BH fit. Full color digital printing on metallic vellum. Hot pink tapes with paint splattered neon green photocopies labels."
Cover artwork by Jack Vater (@drum_pal), Layout and booklet by James Livingston.
